What's going to happen is tomorrow or tonight, depending on the country and the payment type, the issuing bank, in this case chase, is going to send the money from my bank account to the card network, in this case, visa, and then very quickly thereafter, typically within six to 12 hours, the card network will send it to the payment processor. So in this case, Visa sending the money to Worldpay, and then the merchant processor, or payment processor, will settle the funds on that final leg to the fourth party, the merchant, in this case Airbnb.
